<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I just started using arch and for some reason my hard drive was partitioned to 20gb and now I ran out of space in it, I really need more space but cant find a way to unpartition or expand it. </p> <p>Edit. I managed to fix it by reinstalling my linux after backing it up, yes it is rather a harsh way but it worked and the drive is no longer partitioned.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/TherealQuark"> /u/TherealQuark </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wf1r7a/i_just_started_using_arch_and_for_some_reason_my/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wf1r7a/i_just_started_using_arch_and_for_some_reason_my/">[comments]</a></span>